metadata.name: Sākuru #58
metadata.description:
According to Google translate, Sākuru means circle in Japanese.
In this project I take several circles and shuffle their pieces on a grid. While dragging them to their final position I keep their trails (or not).

The project is written in vanilla Javascript.

The drawing is executed at window resolution.

Press '2' to double the resolution. You can press again '2' to double once more;
Press '1' to get back at the window size.
Press 's' to save a png at the current resolution. You can also right click and 'save-as' to obtain the same result.

On mobile devices the program picks the device resolution for rendering (instead of browser available space). This will enable you to save it as png and use it as wallpaper.

It uses 2 external packages, both licensed under MIT license:

* https://www.npmjs.com/package/file-saver
* https://www.npmjs.com/package/alea

metadata.name: Fibonacci Uno #22
metadata.description:
Fibonacci Uno is an algorithm that creates abstract flower drawings.  It draws a series of petals in a radial stack from the bottom up.  The ‘Quantity’, ‘Direction’, and ‘Radii’ features drive the sizes and rhythm of the petals in the stack, and the ‘Palette’, ‘Noise’ and ‘Opacity’ features drive the color story selection and vibes.

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: The Climb #130
metadata.description:
The climb is about the search for purpose.

Everyone needs a purpose, a path that leads somewhere. Whether you reach it or not is not the point, it’s about the climb. The search for a purpose gives our life meaning. It gives us a reason to look for something more.

Unfortunately, there is no universal truth as to what your purpose in life is. Everyone is unique. Different. We are the product of our upbringing, environment and the cumulative sum of thousands of microdecisions. We need to find meaning for ourselves. Our unique meaning. On this path, we climb alone.

“The Climb” is created to be raw, unique, beautiful and violently volatile, much like our lives.


Everything is written in javascript and p5js.
It can sometimes take a little while to render on older computers.

metadata.name: Monsoon #99
metadata.description:
Optimization. It's something that haunts all programmers. Including me. But no longer! Monsoon is a study into the optimization of particle systems for the web. Looking especially deep into dynamic grids and dynamic frame rates.

As for the piece itself, it's a reference to how busy this modern world is. How we're all constantly on the go, whether that is physically, or mentally. Almost feeling like a monsoon. A storm of information. A storm of life. A storm of work. A storm of thoughts. A storm of emotions. A storm of everything. And it's all so fast.

As are the particles. They're all moving around these cyclones of information. Glowing up like neon signs in a busy city. Moving so fast it's almost a blur. Forming into something greater than the sum of its parts.

metadata.name: Influence no.2: Color Memoria #4
metadata.description:
"Color Memoria" is an exploration of colors and algorithms to create an abstract artwork. In this artwork, the relationship between elements and colors has been formed in such a way that a fluid and harmonious state is created. Various densities and more than 12 color palettes have been used.

-----------

- Add &density=2 to 5 to the live view URL to render the image at higher resolution.

- Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.

note:
I highly recommend that you make sure you have enough RAM space and use the Chrome browser or Opera to view the animation in the best possible way. Rendering may take several minutes due to the high density of the artwork.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Even Realer #97
metadata.description:
The simulation simulator. New recipe. Even realer ingredients.

Outputs from fine-tuned model of Stable Diffusion AI to the style of "Contain Real Ingredients", my first NFT collection, consisting of 300 paintings made in The Sims 4 game through 2021/2022. 

Images were cut to resemble the proportion of The Sims 4 canvas and are combined randomly. You have a very small chance of getting an "entire" square image. 

Image composition made with PureSpider template.

metadata.name: Origin-a-tions III: Imagination #120
metadata.description:
The closer we look at things, the more different they will seem to us. The more we try to see what is, the more we will see what is not. Only our Imagination will fill the gap in-between.

Origin-a-tions is a three-parts series of generative artwork, started with Part I: Creation, continued with Part II: Formation, and concluded with Part III: Imagination, that depicts one possible variation of how things may be originating.

* * *

Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART

metadata.name: L-Template #170
metadata.description:
THIS IS NOT AN ARTWORK.

Instead: a framework to store artwork data components onchain by including them as features in the token's smart contract. The stored data are parameters of a Lindenmayer System, which is a formal grammar that was initially conceived of as a theory of plant growth. L-Systems can model complex forms of plants using relatively few simple rules. Custom rules are generated during the minting of each token, based on the transaction hash string. 

The idea is that each iteration of the artwork can be reproduced accurately using an L-System interpreter by accessing the tezos blockchain through the FxHash API (GraphQL) and interpreting token metadata.

Reusable template source: https://github.com/x-terrain/x-terrain.github.io/tree/main/L-Template

Part of an ongoing project with RefractionDAO
